In [2]:
# Load the regular expression library
import re
# Remove punctuation
papers['paper_Title_processed'] =\
papers['Title'].map(lambda x: re.sub('[,\.!?:]', '', x))
# Print out the first rows of papers
papers['paper_Title_processed'].head()

# Convert the titles to lowercase
papers['paper_Title_processed'] =\
papers['paper_Title_processed'].map(lambda x: x.lower())
# Print out the first rows of papers
papers['paper_Title_processed'].head()

# Import the wordcloud library
from wordcloud import WordCloud
# Join the different processed titles together.
long_string = ','.join(list(papers['paper_Title_processed'].values))
# Create a WordCloud object
wordcloud = WordCloud(background_color="white", max_words=5000, contour_width=3, contour_color='steelblue')
# Generate a word cloud
wordcloud.generate(long_string)
# Display the generated image:
# the matplotlib way:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
plt.figure(figsize = (14,10))
plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
plt.axis("off")
